The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 IIT rap

 New Delhi, March 26 (PTI): The comptroller and auditor general (CAG) has pulled up the Indian Institutes of Technology at Delhi, Kharagpur and Mumbai and three other institutes for failing to recover service tax of Rs 1.16 crore from their clients for consultancy services. 

 In its recent report to Parliament, the CAG said the three IITs, the Motilal Nehru National Institute of Technology, Allahabad, National Institute for Industrial Engineering, Mumbai and Visweswaraya National Institute of Technology, Nagpur, deposited the tax from their own funds.




